result.execSummary: Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Continuation of the 1/17/17 Motion Hearing: 
[MK] cases #16CF56 and #16CM32 called at 10:26am. 
Defendant Baltazar  Fuentes in court with Attorney Sylvie Dahnert.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Shawna Stevenoski is sworn as Spanish Interpreter. 
On Motion of ADA Beck, the Court amends the 1/19/17 Amended Information to remove the listing of Case #16CM32 case number in the heading, and to remove the reference to Case #16CM32 as applying to Count #1.
On stipulation of counsel, the Court designates that Case #16CM32 is incorporated into Case #16CF56 and thereafter Case #16CM32 is dismissed. 

Attorney Dahnert concedes that the Rape Shield Law (Statute 972.11) would exclude any evidence of the conduct that the complaining witness engaged in following the alleged sexual assault; the Court no longer needs to address the admissibility of the text messages.  However Attorney Dahnert raises that the SANE nurse exam results validity-issue remains due to the time lapse between the subject allegations and the examination.
The Court admonishes Attorney Dahnert for her failure to formally bring this motion and schedule it for hearing, as is required by Statute and also in the Court's Scheduling Order.  
After hearing arguments, the Court rules that if the State puts in the evidence of bruising, then the Defense will be able to admit the excerpt of the related Civil Case hearing transcript: page 30, line 19 and the following Lines; this will be admitted under the rape shield- exception.  
recess 11:01am.  

NEXT:  (1) Case #16CM32 has been dismissed,  (2) Jury Trial will commence in Case #16CF 56 on Monday at 8:30am.

[MK] cases #16CF56 and #16CM32 called at 8:38am. 
Defendant Baltazar  Fuentes in court with Attorney Sylvie H Dahnert.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Shawna Stevenoski is sworn as Spanish Interpreter. 
Attorney Dahnert indicates that there is no opposition to the State's Motion for Joinder of Crimes. 
The Court grants the Motion for Joinder. The Court directs the State to prepare an Amended Information that includes all charges. 
The Court intends to carry one additional juror; each party will have five strikes during peremptory challenges (23 in the jury box during Jury Selection).
The Court will allow the jurors to take notes and ask written questions of the witnesses.
Attorney Dahnert indicates that there are no Miranda-Goodchild challenges to the State's Notice of Intended Statements of the Defendant.
The Court addresses the State's Motions in Limine
Attorney Dahnert alerts the Court and the State that the Defense intends to attack the validity of the SANE nurse examination; the subject evidence of the Defense on this challenge will consist of text messages.
ADA Beck indicates that, from offer-of-proof provided by Attorney Dahnert, the State has concerns that this may raise rape shield law.
Attorney Dahnert is to provide the subject text messages and the translation into English by end of business today. 
The Court requires to the State to file its response by Thursday [1/19/17] at 9:00am regarding its position concerning admissibility of evidence that it believes falls under the rape shield law.
The Court schedules a further hearing on this Motion for Friday.  The Court denies the request of Atttorney Dahnert to excuse Mr. Fuentes' appearance at this Motion Hearing. 
The Court verifies with Attorney Dahnert, and with Mr. Fuentes individually, that Mr. Fuentes understands that this hearing is his final opportunity for entry of a change-of-plea or other case settlement.  Hereafter the Court intends to proceed to trial. 
Attorney Dahnert 
recess  9:13am. 

NEXT:  (1) Cases are now joined; the State will be filing an Amended Information  (2) Motion Hearing on rape shield issue 1/20/17 at 10:15am,   (3) Jury Trial remains on the calendar for 1/23/17 and 1/24/17, 8:30am-- the JA will contact counsel later this week specify which day(s) the trial will proceed on
